reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality super smooth paper.
reviews.reviewText: This is a very high quality three subject college ruled notebook. It has a nice durable plastic front cover which has a diagonal pocket on the inside. The pocket looks to be attached fairly well, but it honestly looks like it will eventually fail with excessive use. There is a light weight plastic divider between each of the sections and they have front and back bottom pockets on them as well. These pockets feel a bit stronger so I think they will last longer. The rear cover is a piece of heavy duty cardboard and works well for its purpose.The paper is a bit heavier than your typical cheap notebook paper, but not significantly. Where it does differ is in its smoothness. This is super smooth paper that feels almost glassy. The lines on the paper are all well printed and even. The paper is perforated on the edges and the perforations are done well so the pages tear out well when you want them too.The paper takes pencil well as does ink. Ball points and rollerballs work best and neither of them really feather or bleed through excessively. I did test with my fountain pens and really wet inks do tend to bleed through and feather on the paper, but not like the really cheap 25 cent school supply notebooks you get at the beginning of a school year.All said I'm very impressed with it. It's a very reasonable price for this quality of a notebook.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars perfect for class
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice notebook. I like the dividers are plastic folders so they are durable and helpful to hold loose papers. I am not sure how well the back will hold up as it is cardboard but we will see over time. Otherwise works well and is great for my classes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This 3-subject notebook is quite reliable with its sturdy blue plastic cover that effectively protects notes from moisture. The 150 double-sided, wide-ruled sheets offer ample space for various subjects, and the perforation ensures neat tear-outs. The section dividers with pockets are a handy addition for organizing loose papers. While I appreciate the strong wire binding and high-quality paper, it's worth noting that similar products might be available at a lower price locally. Nonetheless, it's a solid choice for students and personal use.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good quality 3-subject spiral notebook for school
reviews.reviewText: The notebook came in a bubble plastic wrap.The 3-subject notebook has 150 sheets in total. The quality of the paper is as good as the notebooks I got from my local retail stores in the past. It is a good school supply for kids.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very serviceable 3-subject notebook
reviews.reviewText: Three-subject notebooks are the preferred notebook for the students in this household. This one does not disappoint. It has a good, sturdy plastic cover and the pocketed dividers are also plastic. The pages are of a nice quality, standard college rule spaced lines, and are perforated for a clean tear. The back cover is of a heavyweight non-corrugated cardboard. Despite this, it does have a slight flop-factor, as shown in the last photo. The aqua color of this notebook is pretty.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is exactly what I was looking for in a 3-subject notebook.* Paper quality is excellent - not too thick, not thin, as you see in some cheaper notebooks.* I like that the cover is plastic - less worry about damaging it.* The dividers are also plastic and there's also a diagonal plastic pocket inside the cover. I can see these dividers lasting, unlike paper dividers.* The sheets of paper have perforations so that it's easy to tear out pages.Overall, this is an excellent notebook at a very reasonable price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a good quality 3 subject notebook. It's just like what you'd get from store shelves for roughly the same price. I ordered the black since that's what my teenager prefers and it helps keep his school work organized without having to carry more items. It's a great option!
